### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
create a regex expression to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm".  The characters can be upper or lower case letters or digits. And the filename extension must be ".usfm".

### Response:


Here's a regex expression that should extract the three character code from the filename "57-1Jn.usfm": 
```
\b[A-Za-z0-9]{2}\D*[A-Za-z0-9]\D*\.\usfm$
```
This regex expression matches any string that starts with two letters or digits, followed by zero or more non-digit characters (which can be either uppercase or lowercase), a hyphen, one or more letters or digits, another hyphen, and ends with the ".usfm" extension.
